The paper focuses on developing a deep learning model for scene text recognition, which involves computer vision (CV) and natural language processing (NLP) tasks. Therefore, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) and cs.CL (Computation and Language) are the most likely sub-categories. The paper also extensively uses deep learning techniques, such as deep convolutional neural networks (CNNs) and long short-term memory (LSTM) networks, which are commonly studied in cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) sub-categories. Finally, the paper discusses the model's ability to process unknown words and arbitrary strings, which is related to information retrieval (IR) tasks, making cs.IR a possible sub-category as well.
